tissueExpression.summary: Normal tissues generally showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic positivity. A subset of renal tubules and fallopian tube displayed strong staining. The lung, spleen and myocytes were mainly negative.

Strong cytoplasmic immunoreactivity was observed in prostate cancer and several cases of ovarian and lung cancer. Skin and testicular cancers were mainly negative. Other malignancies showed weak to moderate cytoplasmic positivity.

tissueExpression.summary: Most of the normal tissues displayed moderate cytoplasmic and occasional nuclear/nucleolar positivity. Strong staining was seen in renal tubules, respiratory epithelia and trophoblastic cells.
Most of the malignant cells displayed moderate cytoplasmic and occasional nuclear/nucleolar positivity. Many cases of lymphomas, gliomas and testicular cancers were negative or weakly stained.
